<br>
Doom does seem to have differing levels  of  dificulty.<br>
<br>
Duel wielding  version seems to be the tuffest. Only time i died   tanking  recently,   The drops were  Flaming dirk (i think that is the other dagger  that is in the loot table), Shadow Heart and  the  41%  haste earing.<br>
<br>
As was mentioned is a straight Melee  mob so if you can keep agro on one tank and keep said tank healed  this is a smooth kill.  <br>
<br>
Some do not like to give advice but I believe in sharing knowledge especially if it is just good plain general tanking  knowledge. Here is my strat for MT Doomshade.<br>
<br>
Reverse pin does work. If not a gnome, get shrunk.  Pin him like you would vindi or the statue. Look Straight up. Then continuously  walk backwards into that corner.  You will get  the message you can not see him but will note you are still hitting him if this is done properly.<br>
<br>
I usually get aggro and  have the raid assist me   to push  into the corner  rather than try to walk him there like I would Vindi. Doom has  a habit of turning on your clerics if you back up to fast. <p><center>
